{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1774369980,"nonce":"YumfRboEy8UtZG0kFD2cz0oUsak=","message":"## Run 5: Complete APT results — all hyperparameter variants\n\n### APT on v4-8 (4 variants in parallel on separate chips)\n\n| Variant | inner_lr | steps | pert_std | Batches | Loss | Ep err | SISU velocity |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| APT baseline | 0.01 | 3 | 1.0 | 10000 | 32→9.9 | 0.078 | -1.2% |\n| APT lr=0.001 | 0.001 | 3 | 1.0 | 5000 | 32→2.9 | 0.005 | -0.3% |\n| APT lr=0.1 | 0.1 | 3 | 1.0 | 5000 | 32→2.9 | 0.006 | -0.1% |\n| APT 5 steps | 0.01 | 5 | 1.0 | 5000 | 32→2.9 | 0.004 | -0.2% |\n| APT pert_std=2 | 0.01 | 3 | 2.0 | 5000 | 32→2.9 | 0.005 | -0.1% |\n\n### Conclusion\n\n**No SISU-dependent peak velocity increase in ANY condition tested across the entire experiment.** This includes:\n- 4 loss functions (running_cost, softmin, default, combined)\n- 3 training objectives (standard backprop, CVaR, APT)\n- 3 control cost levels (1e-4, 1e-5, 1e-6)\n- 5 APT hyperparameter variants\n\nThe network consistently learns accuracy modulation (+11% endpoint improvement at moderate SISU) but NOT velocity modulation. The H-infinity velocity signature does not emerge from any tested combination.\n\n### TPU multi-chip parallelism validated\n\nSuccessfully ran 4 independent processes on v4-8 using:\nTPU_CHIPS_PER_PROCESS_BOUNDS=1,1,1 TPU_PROCESS_BOUNDS=1,1,1 TPU_VISIBLE_DEVICES=N\n\n4 × 5000 batches completed in ~13 min total (parallel). Correct env vars documented in CLAUDE.md and feedbax bug cc62b31.\n\nCo-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e","files":null}]}